                <h4>Adding, Removing, and Reordering Columns</h4>
                <p class="addenda">
                    You can also sort the table by a particular column by clicking the column header to toggle through ascending order, descending order, and unsorted.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div data-youtube="UOf2qbD-LUk" class="hidden">
                <h4>Toggling Errors and Changing Units</h4>
                <p class="addenda">
                    A note about precision: columns without uncertainties are rendered to the best known precision available in the Kepler database.  Columns with uncertainties are rendered to the closest appropriate precision given the associated uncertainty.  For example, the value 10.5123156 &plusmn; 0.2 would be rendered 10.51 &plusmn; 0.2.
                </p>
                <p class="addenda">
                    When changing units the column automatically adjusts the precision to take into account the scaling involved with the unit change.
                </p>
            </div>
